        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 15 at 10:09AM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 1009 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 6 miles northeast of Tuxedo to 11 miles
northeast of Big Country Baptist Assembly to near Crystal Falls.
Movement was south at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Anson, Albany, Hawley, Lueders, Moran, Neinda, Noodle, Ibex, Nugent,
Avoca, Fort Griffin, Funston, The Intersection Of Us-
180 And Ranch Road 126, Mccarty Lake, Tuxedo, Lake Fort Phantom Hill,
The Intersection Of Us-
180 And Farm Road 600, Hodges, Big Country Baptist Assembly, and
Stith.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
